<p>Hey guys i needed some help in framing this query in neo4j.</p>  <p>Rank all artists (music artists) by the unique number of listening users, display the top 5.</p>  <p>Thanks</p>  <p>Graph is like this:</p>  <pre><code>(User)-[:LISTENS_TO{weight:1212}]-&gt;(artists), (User)-[:TAGS]-&gt;(artists), (User)-[:FRIENDS_WITH]-&gt;(friend) </code></pre>  <p>Query that i think might work :</p>  <pre><code>match (m : user) - [l : listnto ] - &gt; a : aryist return count (distinct (m ) )as listncount , a.name order by lostencount desc limit {5} </code></pre>